France Beats Nigeria 1-0 in Opening Match of Women’s Soccer World Cup

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-06-26T14:54:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/france-beats-nigeria-1-0-in-opening-match-of-women-s-soccer-world-cup.html
France  beat Nigeria 1-0 in the
opening match of the Women’s World Cup, with Marie-Laure Delie
getting the only goal in Sinsheim,  Germany .  Host and two-time defending champion Germany plays  Canada 
in today’s other match.  The 16 teams are split into four groups with the top two in
each progressing to the quarterfinals. The final of the four-
yearly  soccer tournament  is on July 17.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  